cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of removing rain from images using a deep network architecture based on deep convolutional and recurrent neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes modifications to the network architecture to better fit the rain removal task, which involves incorporating the squeeze-and-excitation block, indicating a possible focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper conducts experiments on both synthetic and real-world datasets, suggesting a possible focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
